{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_3","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc 'cat TASK.md'","aggregated_output":"# Task: dispatcher-level tests for goal-parallelism enrichment routing (Phase 6)\n\nYou are working ONLY inside this isolated git worktree\n(/tmp/agent-orchestrator-goalparallel-phase6, branch task/phase6-dispatcher-tests,\nalready checked out). Do not touch any other path. Do not push or merge —\na coordinator will do that after independently verifying your diff. This is\na TEST-ONLY task: do not modify any file under `backend/src/`.\n\n## Context\n\nThis backend just landed goal-level parallelism (ADR-001, domain unfreeze\n#12) across several phases. The piece this task covers is untested at its\nown level: `backend/src/app/use_cases/advance_plan.py`'s `PlanDispatcher.advance()`\nmethod (read the whole file first — it's short, ~157 lines).\n\nSpecifically, its cyclic branch (lines ~71-95) was changed so that instead\nof routing to planning only when the single EARLIEST non-terminal goal has\nno tasks yet, it now computes `ready_goal_ids(goals, now)` and routes to\nplanning whenever ANY ready goal still needs enrichment (`goal.id in\nready_ids and not goal.tasks`) — fixing a gap where an earlier-position but\ndependency-blocked goal would otherwise starve a later, independently-ready\ngoal from ever being enriched. When no ready goal needs enrichment, it\nfalls back to `self._execution.handle(plan_id, plan, uow)` exactly as\nbefore this change (this fallback is what keeps a single worker process's\nbehavior byte-identical to before the goal-parallelism work — read the\ninline comment at lines 75-88 for the full reasoning already documented\nthere, and `git log --oneline -20` if you want the fuller commit history\ncontext, especially the commit \"feat(worker): goal-level lease claim +\nadditive execution dispatch (Phase 3c)\" which explains a design correction\nmade mid-implementation).\n\n`PlanDispatcher` (the class) itself has **no dedicated test file today** —\ngrep `backend/tests/` for `PlanDispatcher` to confirm; only the functional\n`advance_plan(...)` entry point (the thin wrapper at the bottom of the same\nfile) gets exercised, indirectly, through other tests. This task adds the\nmissing dispatcher-level coverage for the goal-parallelism-specific routing\ndecision.\n\n## What to test\n\nCreate `backend/tests/unit/orchestration/test_plan_dispatcher.py`. Follow\nexisting conventions in that directory: use the `env_factory` fixture\n(dual-backend memory/sqlite parametrization — read\n`backend/tests/unit/orchestration/conftest.py` and a couple of existing\ntest files like `test_cyclic_worker.py` or `test_aggregate_navigation.py`\nfor the exact fixture/helper patterns already used, so your new tests match\nhouse style rather than inventing a new one) and construct `PlanDispatcher`\ndirectly (it's importable from `src.app.use_cases.advance_plan`).\n\nCover, at minimum:\n\n1. **Later-position ready goal routes to planning even though the\n   earliest-position goal is dependency-blocked.** Construct a cyclic\n   RUNNING plan (an active `Cycle`) with goal A (position 0, `depends_on` a\n   goal that is NOT done — so A is blocked) and goal B (position 1, no\n   deps, `tasks=[]` so it needs enrichment). Provide a `planning_handler`\n   stub/fake to the dispatcher (a minimal object implementing\n   `PhaseHandler`'s `handle(plan_id, plan, uow) -> Signal` — check\n   `src/app/handlers/base.py` for the exact Protocol shape, and whether an\n   existing fake/stub for this already exists in\n   `src/app/testing/fakes.py` or a test file before writing a new one) that\n   records which call it received. Call `dispatcher.advance(plan_id, uow)`\n   and assert the planning handler was actually invoked (this is the\n   dispatcher-level proof; `test_cyclic_worker.py`'s existing\n   `test_enrichment_skips_dependency_blocked_head_goal_for_ready_later_goal`\n   already proves the SAME fan-out fix one layer down, inside\n   `PlanningHandler._next_unenriched` — this new test proves the\n   DISPATCHER's own routing decision, a genuinely different code path, not\n   a duplicate of that test).\n2. **No ready goal needs enrichment -> falls back to execution, not\n   planning.** A cyclic RUNNING plan where every goal already has tasks\n   (already enriched). Assert `dispatcher.advance(...)` calls execution (not\n   the planning handler) — e.g. by giving the dispatcher a `runner` whose\n   task behavior you control (this repo's existing `DummyAgentRunner` /\n   `DummyBehavior` from `src/app/testing/fakes.py` is the established way to\n   script this — read how other execution-handler tests use it) and\n   asserting the runner was actually invoked, OR by asserting the planning\n   handler stub was NOT called while SOME state change consistent with\n   execution happened. Pick whichever assertion is cleanest given the\n   fixtures available; don't over-engineer this one.\n3. **A `planning_handler=None` dispatcher with a goal needing enrichment\n   returns PAUSED, not an exception.** (Matches the existing `if\n   self._planning is None: return Signal.PAUSED` guard at line ~92-93 —\n   confirm this exact behavior with a direct test since nothing today\n   exercises the goal-parallelism branch's None-planning-handler path\n   specifically.)\n4. **All goals terminal -> reaches the existing \"enter review\" path.**\n   Construct a plan where every goal in the active cycle is already\n   terminal (DONE). Call `dispatcher.advance(...)` and confirm it does NOT\n   error and produces the expected review-gate-opening behavior — trace\n   `ExecutionHandler.handle()`'s `if action is None: return\n   self._enter_review(plan_id, plan, uow)` path (grep\n   `execution_handler.py` for `_enter_review` to see exactly what it does\n   and what to assert on the resulting plan/uow state) to know what a\n   correct assertion looks like. If an existing test elsewhere already\n   covers `_enter_review` end-to-end via a different entry point, a lighter\n   assertion here (e.g. \"a review gate opened, or the plan reached\n   AWAITING_REVIEW status\" — whatever `_enter_review` actually does) is\n   fine; don't duplicate a full existing test, just prove the dispatcher's\n   `all(goal.is_terminal ...)` branch reaches it correctly. NOTE: re-read\n   `advance_plan.py`'s actual current code before assuming there's an\n   explicit `all(goal.is_terminal ...)` check in the dispatcher itself —\n   verify exactly how the \"all terminal\" case is currently reached (it may\n   be that `ready_goal_ids` naturally returns empty and `needs_enrichment`\n   is False in this case too, falling through to\n   `self._execution.handle(...)`, which THEN internally detects\n   \"everything's done\" via `peek_next` returning `None` — trace the actual\n   control flow precisely rather than assuming a separate branch exists).\n\n## Verification (run in THIS worktree, its own venv via `uv sync` already done)\n\n```\ncd /tmp/agent-orchestrator-goalparallel-phase6/backend\nuv run ruff check src tests --fix\nuv run mypy src\nuv run pytest -m \"not integration\" -q\nuv run pytest -m integration -q\n```\n\nAll must pass with zero errors. If mypy or any test fails, fix it — do not\nreport success with a failing check. Also explicitly re-run the FULL suite\n(not just your new file) to confirm you haven't broken anything, since this\nis a test-only change but could still collide with existing fixtures/names.\n\n## When done\n\nDelete this TASK.md, commit your changes (no push, no merge). Report back\nunder 400 words: exactly what you added, why each test proves what it\nclaims to prove (tie each assertion back to the specific line(s) in\n`advance_plan.py` it exercises), and the full verification output.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
