{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_26","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc 'git show --stat --oneline cd16906 && git show cd16906 -- backend/src/app/use_cases/advance_plan.py'","aggregated_output":"cd16906 feat(worker): goal-level lease claim + additive execution dispatch (Phase 3c)\n backend/src/app/handlers/execution_handler.py      |  32 +++-\n backend/src/app/testing/fakes.py                   |   5 +\n backend/src/app/use_cases/advance_plan.py          |  26 ++-\n backend/src/app/use_cases/claim_ready_goal.py      |  52 ++++++\n backend/src/app/use_cases/run_worker.py            | 113 ++++++++++--\n .../src/domain/aggregates/planner_orchestrator.py  |  10 +-\n backend/src/domain/repositories/planner_repo.py    |   9 +\n backend/src/infra/db/plan_repository.py            |  14 ++\n backend/src/infra/worker/main.py                   |  27 ++-\n .../orchestration/test_goal_parallel_execution.py  | 196 +++++++++++++++++++++\n .../tests/unit/orchestration/test_worker_loop.py   |  11 +-\n 11 files changed, 465 insertions(+), 30 deletions(-)\ncommit cd1690618dcff418f8afcae3dbf89b7a4833ab1c\nAuthor: guilhermeUpToTask <guilherme256teretelteltel@gmail.com>\nDate:   Wed Jul 22 20:36:34 2026 +0000\n\n    feat(worker): goal-level lease claim + additive execution dispatch (Phase 3c)\n    \n    Wires the goal_leases repository (Phase 3a/3b) into an actual drive loop:\n    Plan.peek_next_for_goal + ExecutionHandler.handle_goal (same body as\n    handle(), goal_id threaded through -- not a divergent reimplementation),\n    PlanRepository.list_running_ids for the candidate scan, claim_ready_goal\n    (the two-step scan-then-claim use case), and drive_goal/goal_tick (the\n    goal-level analogs of drive_plan/worker_tick, sharing a generalized\n    _advance_with_heartbeats instead of each hardcoding a lease repository call).\n    \n    IMPORTANT correction made during this change, worth recording: the first\n    cut made the plan-level dispatcher (advance_plan.py) STOP driving cyclic\n    execution once a ready goal was already enriched, on the theory that\n    goal-level workers would own it -- this broke 5 existing tests and would\n    have broken every current deployment, since no separate goal-level worker\n    loop runs anywhere yet. Corrected to be PURELY ADDITIVE: the plan-level\n    tick keeps driving next_action's single-earliest-ready result exactly as\n    before (byte-identical for a lone worker process), and only gained routing\n    to planning when ANY ready goal needs enrichment (not just the\n    earliest-position one -- the actual fan-out gap, since the dispatcholder's\n    own \"head\" check wasn't ready-aware even after Phase 2 fixed\n    PlanningHandler's internal selection). Separate goal_tick workers\n    concurrently pick up OTHER ready-and-enriched goals the single next_action\n    scan would never reach. run_worker_forever now runs both worker_tick and\n    goal_tick per cycle so one process keeps behaving exactly as before while\n    multiple processes get real cross-process goal parallelism.\n    \n    Also found and fixed a related latent gap surfaced by testing genuinely\n    concurrent goals: Plan.block is still a single plan-wide scalar (correctly\n    NOT reshaped per-goal this phase -- BLOCKED is a whole-plan operator-facing\n    status by design), so two different goals concurrently discovering a\n    block-worthy problem crashed with an uncaught InvalidEditError from\n    open_block's \"already active\" guard. Both _block_on_unpromotable_goal and\n    _pause_on_failed_goal now degrade to a graceful PAUSED when the plan is\n    already blocked, covered by a regression test.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n    Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_017LW1WJzNx4BsdofMmPE61V\n\ndiff --git a/backend/src/app/use_cases/advance_plan.py b/backend/src/app/use_cases/advance_plan.py\nindex a365ce2..5683270 100644\n--- a/backend/src/app/use_cases/advance_plan.py\n+++ b/backend/src/app/use_cases/advance_plan.py\n@@ -18,6 +18,7 @@ from __future__ import annotations\n \n from src.domain.aggregates.planner_orchestrator import Plan, PlanPhase\n from src.domain.repositories.agent_repo import AgentRepository\n+from src.domain.services.navigation import ready_goal_ids\n \n from src.app.handlers.base import PhaseHandler, Signal\n from src.app.handlers.execution_handler import ExecutionHandler\n@@ -60,6 +61,7 @@ class PlanDispatcher:\n         self._execution = ExecutionHandler(runner, agents, workspace, event_sink, clock, verifier)\n         self._gate = GateHandler()\n         self._planning = planning_handler  # injected when the reasoner exists (Phase 2.5)\n+        self._clock = clock\n \n     async def advance(self, plan_id: str, uow: UnitOfWork) -> Signal:\n         with uow:\n@@ -69,12 +71,24 @@ class PlanDispatcher:\n         if plan.active_cycle is not None:\n             if plan.status.value != \"running\" or plan.pause_requested:\n                 return Signal.PAUSED\n-            head = min(\n-                (goal for goal in plan.execution_goals if not goal.is_terminal),\n-                key=lambda goal: goal.position,\n-                default=None,\n-            )\n-            if head is not None and not head.tasks:\n+            goals = plan.execution_goals\n+            # Goal-level parallelism (ADR-001, domain unfreeze #12) is PURELY\n+            # ADDITIVE here: this plan-level tick keeps driving execution\n+            # exactly as it always has (next_action's single-earliest-ready\n+            # result, unchanged since Phase 1) so a lone worker process (no\n+            # separate goal-lease worker running) behaves byte-identically to\n+            # before this unfreeze. The only change is routing to planning\n+            # when ANY ready goal needs enrichment (not just the\n+            # earliest-position one — the actual fix for the fan-out gap\n+            # Phase 2 addressed inside PlanningHandler, but the DISPATCHER\n+            # must also stop assuming \"earliest non-terminal goal has no\n+            # tasks yet\" is the only case that needs a planning tick).\n+            # Separate goal_tick workers (run_worker.py) ADDITIONALLY claim\n+            # and drive OTHER ready-and-enriched goals concurrently — this\n+            # tick never needs to know whether any exist.\n+            ready_ids = ready_goal_ids(goals, self._clock.now())\n+            needs_enrichment = any(goal.id in ready_ids and not goal.tasks for goal in goals)\n+            if needs_enrichment:\n                 if self._planning is None:\n                     return Signal.PAUSED\n                 return await self._planning.handle(plan_id, plan, uow)\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
